The Klein Karoo National Arts Festival held annually in Oudtshoorn has been cancelled amid growing concerns about the spread of the coronavirus. In a statement, management of the festival says it will not continue as planned from 23rd to 29th March. Statement by Klein Karoo National Arts Festival:   They say the decision was not taken lightly and was done in consultation with health authorities, the municipality, sponsors and other stakeholders. Artists and festival-goers who have already purchased tickets and suppliers will be informed of the way forward soon. Latest confirmed coronavirus cases in South Africa: Media Release: LATEST CONFIRMED COVID-19 CASES IN SOUTH AFRICA pic.twitter.com/1oWaklWwy0 â€” Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) March 14, 2020  Confirmed coronavirus cases around the world: 